The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Spain beat India 2-1

Chennai: Hosts India put up a pathetic show to go down 1-2 to defending champions Spain in their opening encounter of the 27th Champions Trophy hockey tournament at the Mayor Radhakrishna Stadium here on Saturday. 

The Spaniards, who exhibited good co-ordination, registered the win through goals by Eduard Tubau (21st minute) and Pablo Amat (52nd minute) to bag three crucial points. 

Kanwalpreet Singh (29th minute) scored the lone goal for India. 

In another match, Olympic champions Australia began their quest for the Champions Trophy with an authoritative 4-1 win over Germany in the opening encounter. 

Jamie Dwyer (14th and 36th), Nathan Eglington (30th) and Brent Livermore (39th) were the scorers for Australia. 

In another match, Pakistan were comprehensively outplayed by the Netherlands 4-1 here. (PTI) 




